  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0db8\u0dd2\u0dbd\u0dca\u0d9a\u0ddd \u0dc4\u0dcf NLDB \u0dc0\u0dd9\u0dad \u0d87\u0db8\u0dad\u0dd2 \u0daf\u0dd4\u0db1\u0dca \u0d8b\u0db4\u0daf\u0dd9\u0dc3",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Minister's advice to Milko and NLDB",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Minister of Agriculture advises to stop the production of skimmed milk by the National Livestock Development Board and Milko institutions and give priority to other milk-related products including liquid milk and powdered milk.",
        "Due to the temporary ban imposed by the government on the import of 300 products, the attention of the Ministry of Agriculture has been focused on producing them locally in order to avoid a shortage in the market of some imported milk-related products.",
        "Accordingly, last Friday the Minister of Agriculture Mahinda Amaraweera discussed with the National Livestock Board and Milko Company.",
        "Currently, the two companies NLDB and Milko are producing many milk related products. Especially buttermilk, liquid milk, cheese, butter, skimmed milk and flavored liquid milk and ice cream are also important among them.",
        "But due to the current shortage of animal feed in the country, the production of liquid milk in the country has dropped by about 34 percent, so the daily amount of liquid milk received by these two companies has greatly decreased.",
        "Therefore, taking into consideration the amount of milk received by those two companies and the importation of milk related products has been suspended, the minister advised not to give priority to the production of skimmed milk and instead to give priority to other milk related products.",
        "Since the production of skimmed milk is a cottage industry, there is enough skimmed milk in the country. But the minister advised the two companies to take that step in order to avoid a shortage of other milk-related products in the market."
      ],
